%pyspark
from pyspark.sql.types import *
#from pyspark.sql.types.DataType import *
from pyspark.sql.functions import split, regexp_extract, lit, concat, when, col, to_date, date_format

%pyspark
meter_weather_1h=spark.read.csv("hdfs://big0.iie.org.mx:9000/JSGP/datasets/london/analytics/meter_weather_1h_tx.csv", header=True, schema = StructType([
                        StructField('ID', IntegerType(), True),
                        StructField('METER_ID', StringType(), True),
                        StructField('TIMESTAMP', StringType(), True),
                        StructField('DATE', StringType(), True),
                        StructField('HD', StringType(), True),
                        StructField('ENERGY', DoubleType(), True),
                        StructField('CAT', IntegerType(), True),
                        StructField('TEMPERATURE', DoubleType(), True),
                        StructField('PRESSURE', DoubleType(), True),
                        StructField('HUMIDITY', DoubleType(), True)]))
meter_weather_1h=meter_weather_1h.withColumn('TIMESTAMP',concat(regexp_extract('TIMESTAMP', r'^(\d{4}-\d{2}-\d{2}).', 1),lit(' '),regexp_extract('TIMESTAMP', r'.T(\d{2}:\d{2}).', 1),lit(':00')))
meter_weather_1h=meter_weather_1h.drop(meter_weather_1h.ID)
meter_weather_1h.cache()
meter_weather_1h.show()

%pyspark
cat_weather_1h=spark.read.csv("hdfs://big0.iie.org.mx:9000/JSGP/datasets/london/analytics/cat_weather_1h_tx.csv", header=True, schema = StructType([

                        StructField('CAT', IntegerType(), True),
                        StructField('TIMESTAMP', StringType(), True),
                        StructField('HD', StringType(), True),
                        StructField('e_sum', DoubleType(), True),
                        StructField('e_avg', DoubleType(), True),
                        StructField('TEMPERATURE', DoubleType(), True),
                        StructField('PRESSURE', DoubleType(), True),
                        StructField('HUMIDITY', DoubleType(), True)]))
                        
cat_weather_1h=cat_weather_1h.withColumn('TIMESTAMP',concat(regexp_extract('TIMESTAMP', r'^(\d{4}-\d{2}-\d{2}).', 1),lit(' '),regexp_extract('TIMESTAMP', r'.T(\d{2}:\d{2}).', 1),lit(':00')))
cat_weather_1h=cat_weather_1h.drop(cat_weather_1h.ID)
cat_weather_1h.cache()
cat_weather_1h.show()
